ext":"When Ultralite.requestControl with a .scroll layout type .. this is the class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"ScrollLayout","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ScrollLayout"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK":{"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this SDK to easily send text and images to your Vuxix smart glasses."}],"kind":"symbol","title":"UltraliteSDK","type":"topic"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller":{"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AutoScroller is a utility class to send a large known block of predfined text to the glasses to be smoothly scrolled."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is simlar to what is seen on a teleprompter or in movie credits.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This class was written using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ScrollLayout"},{"type":"text","text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"duration"},{"type":"text","text":" property."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It can support any language that the font supports.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use "},{"code":"LiveText","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance instead).","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"AutoScroller"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller"}}}